* =E2=80=9CKitsch from the
rich=E2=80=9D in Columbia County: Yesterday, I adventured up to Stair Galle=
ries in Hudson, New York, to beat the late winter malaise. Colin Stair, his=
 daughter, Holly, and their black lab, Kate, were standing near the doorway=
 greeting clients. Most people popping in were local regulars=E2=80=94a mag=
azine editor, jewelry designer, and rug dealer=E2=80=94and, by fun coincide=
nce, Dennis Harrington, head of European furniture at Sotheby=E2=80=99s, wh=
om I=E2=80=99d interviewed ( https://puck.news/sothebys-aso-tavitian-auctio=
n-old-master-paintings-english-furniture/?utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSC=
RIBERS+%283%2F9%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F9%2F2=
5%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617=
da42abd12a ) for my recent story on the Aso O. Tavitian collection.

